parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the GPS system can cause navigation issues, rendering the infotainment system useless, and potentially leading to safety concerns.
symptoms: The infotainment screen displays a message indicating that the system is acquiring its location from GPS satellites
which usually takes less than 10 minutes. The vehicle may require parking in an open area
removal of loose articles near the GPS antenna

and the anti-theft system fails. The vehicle may not start
and the issues may persist despite battery replacement.
